00:42:43,596 --> 00:42:46,360
Here... have a swig.

248
00:42:53,606 --> 00:42:57,167
My dear friend...
I gave you one chance...

249
00:42:58,010 --> 00:43:00,570
But alas... you don't have the guts...

250
00:43:01,180 --> 00:43:04,047
I do dammit...!

251
00:43:05,651 --> 00:43:08,518
That blasted moped got a puncture that day,
else I would have shown you guys.

252
00:43:22,301 --> 00:43:24,861
I can lay down my life
for Dolly... understood?

253
00:43:27,640 --> 00:43:30,541
That'll be the day!
Stop drinking now...

254
00:43:33,913 --> 00:43:36,211
I'm serious... I can
give up my life for her!

255
00:43:36,983 --> 00:43:38,951
Give the bottle first!

256
00:43:41,587 --> 00:43:43,214
I'm not joking... really!

257
00:43:43,589 --> 00:43:46,251
I'll jump into the river!
- Ya ya!

258
00:43:48,928 --> 00:43:50,896
I'll really jump!

259
00:43:51,697 --> 00:43:54,165
No one's holding you back... sissy!

260
00:43:55,902 --> 00:43:57,233
Go jump!

261
00:44:00,606 --> 00:44:02,233
'Dolly' my ass!

262
00:44:05,878 --> 00:44:07,709
Jump... chicken shit!

263
00:44:21,260 --> 00:44:23,524
Bloody hell! You don't know how to swim?!

264
00:44:24,564 --> 00:44:26,191
What the...!

265
00:44:31,571 --> 00:44:36,531
What do you have to say now... brother!

266
00:44:39,645 --> 00:44:42,239
It's not a question of guts...

267
00:44:44,116 --> 00:44:45,879
Its a question of business...

268
00:44:46,619 --> 00:44:51,556
if I run amok, my father's
booze contracts will be snatched.

269
00:44:56,596 --> 00:45:01,226
And you, Brother sir Langda?!
Who are you to talk about nerve?

270
00:45:03,035 --> 00:45:07,062
What guts did you display when Omi
publicly chose Kesu as his successor?

271
00:45:09,809 --> 00:45:13,176
For the last 15 years,

272
00:45:13,546 --> 00:45:17,505
you've been faithfully serving
that half caste on a leg and a half...

273
00:45:19,852 --> 00:45:24,812
Hail Langda General!
Hail General Langda!

274
00:45:29,929 --> 00:45:35,094
That pretender Kesu
comes out of nowhere...

275
00:45:35,568 --> 00:45:39,971
and coolly snatches the
bone out of your mouth.

276
00:45:41,674 --> 00:45:43,972
Where did your guts go walking then?!

277
00:45:45,044 --> 00:45:46,534
Company garden?

278
00:46:00,292 --> 00:46:02,886
You know Rajju,
you are finally making some sense.

279
00:46:03,596 --> 00:46:07,498
Both of us are damned
to lead donkey's lives!

280
00:46:17,543 --> 00:46:19,738
God bless your filthy soul...!

281
00:46:19,879 --> 00:46:21,278
Good lady!

282
00:46:25,351 --> 00:46:27,046
Langda! Help me!

283
00:46:38,898 --> 00:46:40,866
Help me please!

284
00:48:14,260 --> 00:48:18,492
Think I've caught the chill.
The water was freezing.

285
00:48:22,601 --> 00:48:25,161
Look at it this way...
now you know how to swim.

286
00:48:29,542 --> 00:48:34,036
Now I'll teach you how to fly...

287
00:48:37,783 --> 00:48:39,751
like pigeons in the sky.

288
00:48:40,553 --> 00:48:42,521
Bye Bye baby bird...

289
00:48:43,889 --> 00:48:50,055
fly away with Dolly.

290
00:48:53,165 --> 00:48:59,035
Far far away!
To a galaxy someday.

291
00:49:00,039 --> 00:49:02,200
Eh? Eh? Eh?

292
00:49:04,577 --> 00:49:06,477
Buzz off... liar!

293
00:49:08,514 --> 00:49:11,074
If I lie, then I make
love to a filthy bitch...

294
00:49:11,517 --> 00:49:14,145
and if not,
then that bitch is your mother.

295
00:49:21,527 --> 00:49:23,825
And isn't it Mr. Busybody himself?

296
00:49:26,599 --> 00:49:31,036
Lower your eyes while
addressing the new General.

297
00:49:33,205 --> 00:49:36,732
But of course...
my adorable bastard!

298
00:49:41,213 --> 00:49:43,511
I'll slice your tongue out.

299
00:49:44,550 --> 00:49:47,041
In your dreams!
Won't even let you lick it.

300
00:49:50,556 --> 00:49:53,081
Hey Billo Chamanbahar...

301
00:49:57,029 --> 00:49:59,190
You know why I love you Billo baby?

302
00:49:59,832 --> 00:50:00,799
Why?

303
00:50:02,268 --> 00:50:07,729
Cos' you're the biggest tease
in the world.

304
00:50:10,576 --> 00:50:13,101
And you know why
I'm crazy about you?

305
00:50:13,579 --> 00:50:14,546
Hmm?

306
00:50:17,316 --> 00:50:21,218
Cos' you say this to every
third girl you meet... bloody lech!

307
00:50:25,291 --> 00:50:28,021
You still haven't answered.
- What?

308
00:50:29,028 --> 00:50:30,893
Will you marry me?

309
00:50:32,998 --> 00:50:36,229
Let go... creep!

310
00:50:43,108 --> 00:50:48,569
This house hadn't had an heir for years.

311
00:50:50,082 --> 00:50:55,247
Then Pa fell in love and I was born.

312
00:50:58,123 --> 00:51:05,052
My mother belonged to a lower caste...
that's why they call me a half caste.

313
00:51:11,337 --> 00:51:19,301
A crescent, though half,
is still called a moon.

314
00:51:24,917 --> 00:51:25,884
Ouch!

315
00:51:27,252 --> 00:51:28,685
What happened?

316
00:51:29,254 --> 00:51:31,552
My back caught a catch this morning.

317
00:51:55,681 --> 00:51:59,981
What is our new General up to?
Seems to have vanished.

318
00:52:00,219 --> 00:52:02,847
He's at his usual score...
composing duets inside.

319
00:52:07,626 --> 00:52:11,187
General sir!
Grace us with some time please.

320
00:52:12,564 --> 00:52:16,022
Do not forget your subjects
in such a hurry.

321
00:52:20,572 --> 00:52:23,063
Perch your behind please.

322
00:52:23,575 --> 00:52:26,009
What brother Langda?!
Not having any fun?

323
00:52:26,578 --> 00:52:31,072
What should your honour be served with?
- No thanks. My tea's on its way.

324
00:52:31,583 --> 00:52:34,746
Tea?! No hard stuff for our lord?

325
00:52:35,254 --> 00:52:40,886
That's one thing I can't handle, bro.

326
00:52:42,261 --> 00:52:43,626
Uh oh...!

327
00:52:46,765 --> 00:52:47,732
Mental...

328
00:52:48,667 --> 00:52:53,832
Run and get a bottle of milk
for our General here.

329
00:52:56,608 --> 00:52:58,906
And make sure
its one of those nippled ones!

330
00:53:21,633 --> 00:53:24,534
Here... put this on.

331
00:53:26,572 --> 00:53:28,199
Whose jewel is this?

332
00:53:28,373 --> 00:53:32,537
It's not a jewel...
its our family heirloom.

333
00:53:33,579 --> 00:53:37,071
Its adorned the brides
of this house down the ages.

334
00:53:38,584 --> 00:53:40,882
Keep it. It's yours from today.

335
00:53:43,589 --> 00:53:45,557
Treasure it with care!

336
00:53:49,261 --> 00:53:51,821
Put it on and show me first.

337
00:53:54,600 --> 00:53:59,333
First shut your eyes.

338
00:54:10,883 --> 00:54:13,181
Could we have
that 'beedi' number please?

339
00:54:16,588 --> 00:54:19,113
There's a slight problem
with that request.

340
00:54:21,260 --> 00:54:23,228
I've forgotten the words
to that song...

341
00:54:25,898 --> 00:54:28,196
We'd love to be of help.

342
00:54:55,861 --> 00:55:01,891
"No quilt in sight... this cold breeze
arouses the hell out of me."

343
00:55:11,643 --> 00:55:16,512
"It's best to share somebody's quilt."

344
00:55:19,551 --> 00:55:23,851
"Go borrow heat
from the next fellow's oven."

345
00:55:29,628 --> 00:55:36,864
"Light your fags with the heat
of my bosom..."

346
00:55:37,903 --> 00:55:40,303
"its burning up inside me!"

347
00:56:01,927 --> 00:56:08,833
"Let smoke not slip out of your lips...
the world's smoked out already!"

348
00:57:09,961 --> 00:57:17,163
"No crime's been charged...
why do I still feel sentenced to death?"

349
00:57:17,903 --> 00:57:21,498
"Haul me to your court one afternoon."

350
00:57:21,873 --> 00:57:25,502
"Handcuff me with my anklets."

351
00:57:25,877 --> 00:57:30,177
"Haul me up in the afternoon"

352
00:57:31,983 --> 00:57:36,181
"Sentence me... punish me severely."

353
00:57:40,225 --> 00:57:47,188
"Light your stoves with the heat of
my bosom..."

354
00:57:48,266 --> 00:57:50,530
"its burning up inside me!"

355
00:58:35,881 --> 00:58:42,514
"No knife's sharp
enough to match your nibbles."

356
00:58:47,826 --> 00:58:52,854
"The way you leave
your teeth marks behind..."

357
00:58:53,565 --> 00:58:58,867
"farmers would forget
how to cut their crops"

358
00:58:59,671 --> 00:59:04,199
"Please Billo... would you settle down
with a brute like this?"

359
00:59:23,528 --> 00:59:28,158
"Nobody warned me...
nobody woke me up."

360
00:59:31,736 --> 00:59:36,503
"Suddenly you come into my quilt..."

361
00:59:39,644 --> 00:59:43,910
"trying to impress me
with your clove breath."

362
00:59:46,551 --> 00:59:53,514
"Burn your coals with the heat of
my bosom..."

363
00:59:54,025 --> 00:59:56,585
"its burning up inside me!"

364
01:00:12,577 --> 01:00:16,536
"It's best to share somebody's quilt..."

365
01:00:20,118 --> 01:00:29,891
"go borrow heat from
the next fellow's oven."

366
01:00:35,767 --> 01:00:37,564
Bastard! I'd asked you not to smoke!

367
01:01:01,626 --> 01:01:04,288
Let go man... you're piss drunk!

368
01:01:27,285 --> 01:01:28,718
Brother Omi...

369
01:02:04,723 --> 01:02:08,591
Is somebody going to bloody own up?

370
01:02:11,329 --> 01:02:17,097
Who the hell started
this brawl? Langda?

371
01:02:24,643 --> 01:02:28,807
Let it go Omi bro...
We'll sort it in the morning.

372
01:02:30,582 --> 01:02:34,074
Don't rush to your grave...
answer the bloody question.

373
01:02:35,286 --> 01:02:37,254
Whose fault was it?

374
01:02:43,795 --> 01:02:45,763
It was booze.

375
01:02:48,833 --> 01:02:52,098
Partly booze... partly my fault!

376
01:02:54,973 --> 01:02:58,932
This poor child had warned me
that he can't hold his drink...

377
01:03:02,414 --> 01:03:04,905
I fingered him and he got plastered.

378
01:03:06,951 --> 01:03:09,112
I should be punished... not him!

379
01:03:17,562 --> 01:03:23,194
General! Its neither booze...
nor Langda!

380
01:03:24,602 --> 01:03:29,062
It's my fault... for having
chosen you as the General!

381
01:03:32,644 --> 01:03:40,551
Stay out of my sight for a few days
else I'll skin you alive.

382
01:03:59,971 --> 01:04:03,566
Don't worry.
Omi's anger is like camphor.

383
01:04:05,376 --> 01:04:07,742
It'll vanish in no time... eat something.

384
01:04:11,549 --> 01:04:12,516
Not bad!

385
01:04:12,717 --> 01:04:14,912
I've been toiling away
at these chappatis...

386
01:04:15,220 --> 01:04:17,188
and nobody cares a shit!

387
01:04:17,589 --> 01:04:20,820
Why are you taking it out on the food?
Eat up now!

388
01:04:23,561 --> 01:04:31,525
If your face stays bloated like this
the fat chappatis will start blushing.

389
01:04:34,839 --> 01:04:38,639
Not bad at all!
That's a rare smile in this weather...

390
01:04:39,711 --> 01:04:42,202
Don't worry... I'll speak to Brother Omi.

391
01:04:42,580 --> 01:04:44,548
"I'll speak to Brother Omi"

392
01:04:45,884 --> 01:04:48,250
And he'll listen to you?! Surely...!

393
01:04:50,755 --> 01:04:56,887
Now Omi's not going to listen to anyone.

394
01:04:59,597 --> 01:05:02,225
There's only one voice
of reason that can help...

395
01:05:03,601 --> 01:05:05,159
Dolly's voice.

396
01:05:07,872 --> 01:05:11,171
And if I'm not mistaken,
isn't she a bum chum of yours?

397
01:05:13,077 --> 01:05:16,911
We're visiting Bhaisaab over the next
2-3 days... some election work.

398
01:05:17,582 --> 01:05:20,016
By the time we're back,
get Dolly in the loop.

399
01:05:21,553 --> 01:05:22,520
Cool?

400
01:05:22,720 --> 01:05:24,517
It's cooler than the coolest!

401
01:05:24,823 --> 01:05:27,257
Now... lets see those molars.

402
01:05:30,728 --> 01:05:34,528
Have you ever fed me...
with half this love?

403
01:05:35,300 --> 01:05:36,790
Bugger off!

404
01:05:44,242 --> 01:05:47,040
Don't panic now! I'll be there soon.

405
01:05:50,782 --> 01:05:53,546
Auntyji's worried about my safety.

406
01:05:55,286 --> 01:05:59,552
The C.I. D says that I might be attacked.

407
01:06:05,730 --> 01:06:08,893
She wants me to come to the capital
for 2-3 days... till it tides over.

408
01:06:10,602 --> 01:06:12,502
2-3 days?!

409
01:06:13,872 --> 01:06:16,841
In the meantime, we can start
fund raising by ourselves... right?

410
01:06:23,548 --> 01:06:28,850
Sounds fine.
Then?

411
01:06:32,557 --> 01:06:34,525
Pull the chain son.

412
01:06:45,103 --> 01:06:47,071
Any problem Bhaisaab?

413
01:06:47,572 --> 01:06:52,271
Reverse the train.
These gentlemen have to be dropped back.

414
01:06:53,344 --> 01:06:54,538
Sorry?

415
01:06:55,580 --> 01:06:56,945
You heard me!

416
01:06:57,148 --> 01:07:01,551
Golu! When you feel like a glass of juice,
what do you do?

417
01:07:01,953 --> 01:07:03,921
I massage Omi Uncle's head!

418
01:07:06,758 --> 01:07:11,092
And Indu, when you want a new sparkler,
what do you do?

419
01:07:11,696 --> 01:07:14,494
Heaven only knows!
Have to massage half a leg all night!

420
01:07:18,202 --> 01:07:20,500
So your job will be done...

421
01:07:21,873 --> 01:07:25,673
But it's not gonna be for free...
What say Kesu sir?!

422
01:07:26,144 --> 01:07:28,112
Whatever her highness demands.

423
01:07:28,546 --> 01:07:30,514
It's a deal then?
- Deal.

424
01:07:40,959 --> 01:07:42,517
Now you sing.

425
01:07:51,636 --> 01:07:55,538
Everything else's fine...
except its pronounced 'bottom'.

426
01:08:04,582 --> 01:08:07,016
That's what I said-'bottom'.

427
01:08:07,952 --> 01:08:11,217
Fine! Will do!
- What now?

428
01:08:53,331 --> 01:08:54,958
Shit! Omi bro's back!

429
01:08:55,233 --> 01:08:58,532
Langda said they'll be back in 2-3 days.
I'm screwed now!

430
01:08:58,903 --> 01:09:01,531
Hang on!
Lets sort this once and for all.

431
01:09:01,973 --> 01:09:04,874
No way! He'll skin me alive
and hang it out to dry!

432
01:09:15,186 --> 01:09:17,154
Wasn't that Kesu?

433
01:09:21,192 --> 01:09:24,491
